"settings.privacy_policy" = "Privacy Policy";
"settings.privacy_policy.message" = "PRIVACY POLICY\n\nLast updated: June 1, 2026\n\n1. Introduction\nThis Privacy Policy describes how World of Fables, an educational app for children designed to develop story comprehension, logical sequencing, attention, and visual memory, handles information. The app is designed according to the principles of data minimization and privacy by design.\n\n2. Data Controller\nThe Data Controller is Marcello Guida. For privacy matters, please contact: mguida2604@gmail.com.\n\n3. Personal data and methods of collection\nThe app does not require registration or login and does not collect names, surnames, email addresses, telephone numbers, postal addresses, location data, IP addresses, device identifiers, operating system information, usage logs, or other identifying information. It does not create user profiles.\n\nThe app saves only non-personal preferences and gameplay progress locally on the device using Apple's UserDefaults storage. These may include completed levels, unlocked areas, current gameplay position, selected language, accessibility preferences, music settings, animation settings, and haptic settings.\n\nIf a user or a parent or guardian voluntarily contacts support by email, the sender's email address and any information included in the message will be processed solely to respond to the request.\n\n4. Purposes and legal bases under the GDPR\nLocal settings and progress are used only to provide the app's requested functionality and preserve the user experience. They are not transmitted to the Data Controller.\n\nAny support email is processed to respond to the user's request and, where applicable, to take pre-contractual steps at the user's request or pursue the Data Controller's legitimate interest in providing assistance, pursuant to Article 6(1)(b) and Article 6(1)(f) GDPR. Data may also be processed where necessary to comply with a legal obligation or protect the Data Controller's rights, pursuant to Article 6(1)(c) and Article 6(1)(f) GDPR.\n\n5. Camera and augmented reality\nThe app includes an optional augmented reality feature. Subject to the user's device permission, the camera is used only to display story cards in the user's surroundings through ARKit. Camera input is processed locally on the device. The app does not record, save, upload, or share photos, videos, or camera data. Camera permission may be denied or revoked at any time in the device settings.\n\n6. Security and retention\nLocal preferences and progress remain on the device and can be removed by resetting progress in the app, uninstalling the app, or using the device's available controls. Support emails are retained only for the time necessary to answer the request, meet applicable legal obligations, or protect the Data Controller's rights. Appropriate technical and organizational measures are adopted in relation to the limited processing performed.\n\n7. Third parties, remote storage, and international transfers\nThe app does not send user or device data to the Data Controller, external servers, cloud databases, hosting services, partners, or third parties. It does not transfer app data outside the European Economic Area. Email messages voluntarily sent to support are handled through the email services used by the sender and the Data Controller; the relevant providers' terms and privacy policies apply and may provide for processing outside the European Economic Area in accordance with applicable law.\n\n8. Cookies, tracking, analytics, and advertising\nThe app does not use cookies, tracking technologies, third-party analytics SDKs, advertising networks, sponsored content, or behavioral advertising.\n\n9. Features not included\nThe app does not include user accounts, external authentication services, push notifications, purchases, payments, subscriptions, or external payment mechanisms.\n\n10. Children's privacy\nThe app is intended for children but does not collect personal data from children. The support contact is intended for parents or guardians. Children should not send personal information by email. If personal data relating to a child is received unintentionally, a parent or guardian may request its deletion by contacting the Data Controller.\n\n11. User rights\nWhere the Data Controller processes personal data, users may exercise the rights provided by Articles 15-22 GDPR, where applicable: access, rectification, erasure, restriction of processing, objection, data portability, and withdrawal of consent without affecting prior lawful processing. Users may also lodge a complaint with the competent supervisory authority, including the Italian Data Protection Authority (Garante per la protezione dei dati personali).\n\n12. Exercising privacy rights and contacts\nTo exercise privacy rights or request information, please contact Marcello Guida at mguida2604@gmail.com. Requests will be handled in accordance with applicable law.\n\n13. Changes to this Privacy Policy\nThis Policy may be updated if the app or applicable legal requirements change. Any new processing will be described before it is introduced. The updated version will be made available in the app.";

